programme.title: Underworld

programme.desc: A bright college student is haunted by her past in this thriller. Katie Burke is a driven senior at a prestigious college whose boyfriend, Embry, vanished years earlier. Katie's life unravels when a cop investigates the disappearance and Embry begins showing up on campus

programme.title: Erin Brockovich
programme.desc: Erin Brockovich is an unemployed single mother, desperate to find a job, but is having no luck.While no one takes her seriously, with her trashy clothes and earthy manners, that soon changes when she begins to investigate a suspicious real estate case involving the Pacific Gas & Electric Company. What she discovers is that the company is trying quietly to buy land that was contaminated by hexavalent chromium, and, in turn, poisoning the residents in the area. As she digs deeper, Erin finds herself leading point in a series of events that would involve her lawfirm in one of the biggest class action lawsuits in American history against a multi-billion dollar corporation

programme.title: Taking Woodstock
programme.desc: Demetri Martin stars in this historical comedy-drama about the celebrated 1969 festival of peace and love. Martin plays Elliot Teichberg, an interior designer who offers to help out the promoters of Woodstock when they lose their permit to have the concert. He provides a space for the show, but must think on his feet when the entire event becomes much larger than he imagined. Directed by Ang Lee. Eugene Levy, Emile Hirsch, Liev Schreiber

programme.title: Big Business
programme.desc: Farce with Bette Midler and Lily Tomlin as two sets of twins separated at birth. Roone: Fred Ward. Graham: Edward Herrmann. Fabio: Michele Placido. Chuck: Daniel Gerroll. Michael: Barry Primus. Directed by Jim Abrahams

programme.title: The Eiger Sanction
programme.desc: An ex-hit man is lured out of retirement to kill a climber ascending a mountain in the Swiss Alps. Trouble arises, however, when the target's true identity remains obscured

programme.title: The Verdict
programme.desc: An alcoholic lawyer thinks he can make some quick cash getting a settlement for the family of a woman who is in a coma after being operated on at a Catholic hospital. However, he becomes emotionally involved in the case, turns down the offer, and takes the powerful institution to court

programme.title: Lowriders
programme.desc: An aimless young street artist in L.A. named Danny finds himself torn between the lowrider car culture of his father and his desire for a creative outlet. This generational clash is further complicated when Danny's older brother returns home from prison

programme.title: The Good Lie
programme.desc: A group of Sudanese refugees arrive in Kansas and are met by Carrie Davis, a no-nonsense employment agency counsellor who has been tasked with helping find them jobs. Together with her boss, Jack, she helps them rebuild their shattered lives

programme.title: The Thin Red Line
programme.desc: World War II epic follows a squad of GIs advancing on Guadalcanal. One solider, Private Witt, is a deserter living in peace and harmony with the natives of a Pacific island paradise. However, Witt's respite from war is brief as he's captured by the Navy and forced back into combat

programme.title: The Hunted
programme.desc: A rogue special-forces soldier is tracked down by his former mentor in this action thriller starring Benicio del Toro stars as Aaron Hallam, one of the U.S. military's most skilled hand-to-hand combat operatives. In the years following his successful assassination of a Serbian warlord in late-'90s Kosovo, Hallam finds himself plagued by traumatic flashbacks of death and destruction, so much so that when he finally returns home, he regresses into a feral, survivalist state in the woods of the Pacific Northwest. There, he deliberately and elaborately hunts and kills poachers who happen to cross his path. When the FBI investigates the murders, they call in the man who taught Hallam everything he knows: retiree L.T. Bonham (Tommy Lee Jones). As the instructor pursues his unhinged former pupil, Bonham begins to learn about key events in Hallam's life that pushed him over the edge

programme.title: Sully
programme.desc: This biopic of airline pilot Chesley "Sully" Sullenberger depicts his successful emergency landing of an Airbus A320 on the Hudson River in January 2009. In the aftermath of this unprecedented feat, he must endure the weight of sudden fame, second-guessing by investigators and his own doubts about his actions that fateful day

programme.title: Nell
programme.desc: A young woman living in an isolated North Carolina cabin is discovered by a small-town doctor, who is fascinated by her and attempts to introduce her to the world. Based on the play "Idioglossia" by Mark Handley

programme.title: Jersey Boys
programme.desc: This musical drama chronicles the rise and fall of Frankie Valli and the Four Seasons, one of the key pop groups of the early '60s, responsible for such iconic hits as "Sherry," "Walk Like a Man" and "Big Girls Don't Cry."

programme.title: Jersey Boys

programme.title: 17 Again
programme.desc: A former high-school basketball star gets a second shot at life after he's miraculously transformed back into a teenager. Back in high school, Mike O'Donnell was an MVP. But then Mike sacrificed everything in order to stay by his expectant girlfriend Scarlett. Twenty years later, Mike's life is falling apart when he's suddenly transported back into his teenage body and he discovers that by trying to recapture his best years, he could risk losing it all

programme.title: About a Boy (2002)
programme.desc: Adaptation of the Nick Hornby novel about the friendship that develops between a bright but awkward 12-year-old boy and a wayward thirtysomething man masquerading as a lone parent in a bid to seduce single mothers. Ironically, it is the boy who initiates the bachelor into the world of adult responsibility and meaningful relationships as the bond between them deepens

programme.title: Heaven Can Wait
programme.desc: Warren Beatty in a remake ("Here Comes Mr. Jordan") about a dead athlete who returns to Earth in another body. Buck Henry, Julie Christie, James Mason, Jack Warden, Dyan Cannon, Charles Grodin. Krim: Vincent Gardenia. Sisk: Joseph Maher. Bentley: Arthur Malet. Beatty and Henry codirected. Scripted by Beatty and Elaine May

programme.title: Crimes and Misdemeanors
programme.desc: A married New York ophthalmologist tries to break up with his mistress, who threatens to tell his wife. Meanwhile, his mob-connected brother offers to "make the problem go away."

programme.title: High Plains Drifter
programme.desc: Clint Eastwood's first Western as both director and star is a revenge tale that centers on a mysterious stranger who rides into a lakefront settlement, where the citizens beg him to defend them against a group of outlaws who have a score to settle with the townsfolk

programme.title: The Mummy
programme.desc: Fantasy adventure about the search for buried treasure protected by an ancient mummy's curse in the Egyptian desert. An American mercenary who knows the treasure's secret location is rescued from a Cairo prison by an English historian and her brother. Racing against unscrupulous rivals, they head into the desert, where they encounter flesh-eating scarab beetles, killer sandstorms and reincarnated demons

programme.title: Invincible
programme.desc: The story of the misfit outsider who rises through the ranks of a professional sport to enjoy inexplicable success has been stamped into celluloid more times than most folks can remember. INVINCIBLE tells the tale of bartender Vince Papale, a down-on-his-luck former teacher who decides to answer an open tryout for the Philadelphia Eagles. It doesn't take a genius to work out what happens next, but the twist here is that Vince Papale is a real person..

programme.title: Empire
programme.desc: Gangster thriller following a New York drug dealer who hopes to make a legal fortune on Wall Street. When a stockbroker offers him a business proposal, he thinks this will be his chance to go out on top, but soon finds out that he has been double-crossed and his last option is to get revenge

programme.title: The Ghost Writer
programme.desc: A British screenwriter (Ewan McGregor) agrees to ghostwrite the memoirs of a retired prime minister, but after he takes the job the former political leader is accused of committing a war crime. As the writer uncovers facts that corroborate these suspicions, he begins to fear he might be killed, just like the man who worked on the memoirs before him. Directed by Roman Polanski. Pierce Brosnan, Tom Wilkinson, Olivia Williams

programme.title: Mickey Blue Eyes

programme.title: Mission
programme.desc: Brian De Palma directed this first instalment of the action thriller franchise that rebooted the American TV series (which ran from 1966 to 1973). Tom Cruise stars as agent Ethan Hunt, member of America's elite IMF team (that's the undercover spies of the Impossible Mission Force; not the financiers of the International Monetary Fund). Hunt and a group of colleagues are sent to Prague to both prevent a list of undercover agents' real identities from being disclosed, and to reveal who within the IMF has turned traitor. But things go disastrously wrong and all but one of the team are massacred. As the sole survivor, Hunt must now try to prove his innocence and discover the real betrayer before he is terminated by his own government. And thus begins a top-class, high-octane chase thriller, packed with jaw-dropping special effects and stunts

Over the course of the next century the two immerse themselves in a series of major conflicts, right up to the Vietnam War, where they are recruited by Major Stryker to join Team X: a killing machine staffed by other mutants. programme.desc: Inspired by The Canterbury Tales, as well as the story of Ulrich von Lichtenstein, this is the story of William, a young squire with a gift for jousting. William, lacking a proper pedigree, convinces Chaucer to forge genealogy documents that will pass him off as a knight. With his newly-minted history in hand, the young man sets out to prove himself a worthy knight at the country's jousting competition, and finds romance along the way

programme.desc: Jorge Blanco's animation is as witty and family-friendly as you'd expect from a film that's written by Joe Stillman, who also wrote Shrek and Shrek 2. Astronaut Chuck Baker lands on Planet 51, expecting to plant a flag, hit a few golf balls and go home. of 1950s America, complete with a fascination with alien-invasion films. But this planet is inhabited by small, green aliens (is there any other kind?) whose society mirrors that The aliens are therefore terrified by their 'invader', just as he is by them. Only teenage astronomer Lem (Justin Long) appears unperturbed. He befriends Chuck and, in shades of ET, hides him in his home, before they embark on a journey to get Chuck back to his ship before it returns to Earth. There's plenty for kids and parents alike to enjoy in this affectionate dig at 50s society. Vocal talents include Gary Oldman, Seann William Scott, Jessica Biel and John Cleese

programme.title: X-Men
programme.desc: (2000) Bryan Singer's fantasy film is set on a parallel Earth where humans reluctantly live alongside mutants, those with genetic "defects" that give them superhuman powers. The mutants are gathered into two camps. Those at Professor Charles Xavier's (Patrick Stewart) school are taught to curb their powers and use them for good, while his opposite number, Magneto (Ian McKellen), believes that humans want to destroy them and is assembling a force to win the day by turning the world's leaders into mutants. The film concentrates on Wolverine and Rogue (Hugh Jackman, Anna Paquin), who side with Xavier as the two factions launch into climactic battle. Edited for language and violence ; HD Wide

programme.desc: Hugh Grant and Julia Roberts star in Roger Michell's BAFTA Award-winning and hugely popular comedy romance, scripted by Richard Curtis (Four Weddings and a Funeral). Anna Scott is the most famous actress in the world; William Thacker runs a struggling second-hand bookshop in Notting Hill. After colliding in the street they begin a relationship, which is soon fraught with complications as the tabloid press hound Anna, and William must summon all his charm, ingenuity and patience if there is to be a happy ending. A great cast provides additional comedy, including Rhys Ifans as Grant's spectacularly unhygienic flatmate

programme.desc: Garry Marshall's romantic-comedy stars Julia Roberts as Maggie Carpenter, who has apparently left seven, maybe eight, grooms at the altar. USA Today journalist Ike Graham uses her as an example for a female-bashing piece, only for Carpenter to angrily reply that she only jilted three men, and that's just one of 15 inaccuracies in his piece. Stung by the rebuke, Graham travels to Carpenter's small home town to get the story directly from her. But when the pair meet, it's apparent wedding bells might soon be ringing again... With Joan Cusack, Hector Elizondo, Rita Wilson and Christopher Meloni

programme.title: My Best Friend's Wedding
programme.desc: Nine years ago Julianne Potter and Michael O'Neal made that mysterious transition from lovers to 'Just Friends'. It is an arrangement that still appeals to Julianne whose idea of commitment is measured in days rather than years, even if it left Michael still carrying the proverbial torch. Best friends since that fateful day in college, they made a pact that if neither had found someone to love by the age of 28 they would marry each other. It seemed like a goof a the time ...except that maybe one of them wasn't joking. Now it's their 28th year of life, and Michael just popped it to someone else

programme.title: The Lord of the Rings
programme.desc: In the mythical Middle-earth, a fantastic, mysterious world inhabited by men, Hobbits, wizards, elves, dwarfs and Trolls, lives Frodo Baggins (Elijah Wood), a shy Hobbit who must accomplish a difficult mission to save his land's destiny. It all begins when Frodo receives a ring from his uncle Bilbo (Ian Holm) and wizard Gandalf (Ian McKellen) discovers it is the Unique Ring itself. This powerful ring has been conceived by Sauron, the dark Lord of Mordor (Sala Baker), and with it, it is possible to enslave the whole of the Middle-earth through the use of dark forces. To destroy the ring, Frodo must take it to a distant mountain in Mordor, a region controlled by the Master of Evil. Fortunately, he is accompanied by a group formed by Hobbits Sam (Sean Astin), Merry (Dominic Monaghan) and Pippin (Billy Boyd), as well as Gandalf, the human warriors Aragorn (Viggo Mortensen) and Boromir (Sean Bean), and elf Legolas (Orlando Bloom). Together they have to confront dangerous obstacles in a frightening world of mystery and darkness. This spectacular adaptation of J.R.R. Tolkien's epic trilogy was directed by Peter Jackson

programme.desc: Oscar-nominee Joaquin Phoenix plays Johnny Cash, and Oscar-winner Reese Witherspoon plays June Carter in James Mangold's acclaimed biographical film about country music's legendary 'Man in Black'. The film follows Cash from his childhood, where he was touched by tragedy, through his years on the road to his marriage to June Carter, who was country royalty (having been a part of the massively influential Carter Family band), and their struggle to find happiness as she weans him off booze and drugs. Walk the Line is a warts-and-all biopic, showing Cash's faults as well as his undoubted star quality as one of the greatest singer/songwriters that America has ever produced(n)

programme.title: The American
programme.desc: Academy Award winner George Clooney stars in the title role of this suspense thriller, filmed on location in Italy. Alone among assassins, Jack (played by Mr. Clooney) is a master craftsman. When a job in Sweden ends more harshly than expected for this American abroad, he vows to his contact Larry (Bruce Altman) that his next assignment will be his last. Jack reports to the Italian countryside, where he holes up in a small town and relishes being away from death for a spell. The assignment, as specified by a Belgian woman, Mathilde (Thekla Reuten of 'In Bruges'), is in the offing as a weapon is constructed. Surprising himself, Jack seeks out the friendship of local priest Father Benedetto (Italian stage and screen veteran Paolo Bonacelli) and pursues romance with local woman Clara (Italian leading lady Violante Placido). But by stepping out of the shadows, Jack may be tempting fate(n)
